ontrol the carousel externally by passing the `ref` prop to the `Carousel` component and using the `emblaApi` to control the carousel imperatively."},"40":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-16","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#external-controls-controlled","content":"You can control the carousel externally by using the `activeIndex` prop to control the active slide index."},"41":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-17","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#hide-controls","content":"The hide controls carousel is a carousel that hides the navigation controls."},"42":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-18","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#variable-widths","content":"It supports multiple slides with different widths."},"43":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-19","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#events","content":"You can listen to events like `onChange`, `onPrev`, or `onNext`."},"44":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-20","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#rtl-direction","content":"The carousel follows the current **layout direction** (LTR or RTL). By default, that direction is detected automatically from the browser or system settings."},"45":{"id":"/docs/components/button","page_id":"/docs/components/button","type":"page","content":"Button","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/button"},"46":{"id":"/docs/components/button-0","page_id":"/docs/components/button","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/button","content":"The Button component allows users to initiate actions or submit forms with a single click"},"47":{"id":"/docs/components/button-1","page_id":"/docs/components/button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/button#insta