-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"973":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"974":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"975":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system."},"976":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"page","content":"Flex","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex"},"977":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/flex","content":"One-dimensional layout component for arranging children in rows or columns with alignment and spacing control"},"978":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex#installation","content":"Installation"},"979":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layou